Covid-19 track and tracing teams' biggest headaches over the past year included patients giving the wrong contact details and team members falling ill themselves, provincial officials told TimesLIVE. This led to many positive cases not being traced, and an uncountable number of people getting infected after coming in contact with those not knowing they had the virus. This transpired from interviews with provincial officials looking back over the past year since SA experienced its first Covid-19 case.